div.p:
The record of representations and replies which we have under consideration for publication include this Government’s formal note to the Japanese Government dated March 30, 1939;
Foreign Relations. Japan, 1931–1941, Vol. i, p. 643. oral representations made May 11, 1939, to the Japanese Foreign Minister by you;See memorandum by the Ambassador in Japan, May 11, 1939,
ibid., p. 646. the Japanese Government’s reply of May 17, 1939;See telegram No. 238, May 19, 1939, 4 p.m., from the Chargé in Japan, ibid., p. 649. to this Government’s note of March 30, 1939; this Government’s formal note to the Japanese Government dated May 22, 1939;See telegram No. 241, May 22, 1939, 6 p.m., from the Chargé in Japan, ibid., p. 650. Mr. Dooman’s representations to the Foreign Minister of June 19, 1939;See telegram No. 283, June 19, 1939, 7 p.m., Foreign Relations, 1939, Vol. iv, p. 342. and your note of September 13, 1940 (referred to in your 837, September 14, 9 a.m.), which the Department would appreciate receiving by radio via Shanghai in full text.
